    "body": "> On key generation in prysm itself, it will be unlikely that we will be adding it in at the current stage. Pre- beacon-chain launch, we made the decision not to have prysm generate keys/wallets but instead only be able to import/recover. Users would use the staking cli to generate new keys and prysm would then import those. On keeping the dependency chain minimal, underneath Prysm depends on quite a few wealdtech/attestant libraries to handle the respective wallets. So underneath Prysm would still use wealdtech/attestant libraries to generate new keys if we were ever to have the feature \r\n-nishant\r\n\r\nwe can keep this one open to continue the discussion here.\r\n\r\n",
